|wi1_chip2_brand=Airgo |wi1_chip2_model=AGN100RF |wi1_chip3_brand=Airgo |wi1_chip3_model=AGN100RF |wi1_802dot11_protocols=bg |wi1_ant_conn=U.FL |wi1_txchains=2 |wi1_rxchains=3 |wi1_sstreams=2 |wi2_module= |wi2_module_if= |wi2_chip1_brand= |wi2_chip1_model= |wi2_chip2_brand= |wi2_chip2_model= |wi2_chip3_brand= |wi2_chip3_model= |wi2_802dot11_protocols= |wi2_ant_conn= |wi2_txchains= |wi2_rxchains= |wi2_sstreams= |eth_none= |eth_cpu=true |eth_chip1_brand= |eth_chip1_model= |eth_chip2_brand= |eth_chip2_model= |eth_chip3_brand= |eth_chip3_model= |sw_cpu=true |sw_brand= |sw_model= |lan_speed=100M |lan_ports=4 |wan_ports=1 |addl_chips= |flags= |tp_firmware= |802dot11_protocols=bg |default_ssid=Belkin_Pre-N_XXXXXX |default_ssid_regex=^Belkin_Pre-N_[0-9A-F]{6}$ |default_ip=192.168.2.1 |default_user= |default_pass= |oui=00:11:50 |oui_eth=00:11:50 }} The device has been tagged with the AGN100 wireless module FCC ID.. but the only FCC ID printed on the unit is SA3-AGN0901AP0100. SA3-AGN0901AP0100 defines the board used in the Belkin F5D8230-4 v1 which is not used in the v2.. so the FCC ID printed on the label is incorrect.
The RF side is not shielded on this model (differing from the v1 and other models sharing the same OEM model).
The default SSID is '''Belkin_Pre-N_XXXXXX''' where '''XXXXXX''' appears to be the last three octets of the LAN MAC address (upper case letters).
